## Step 3: Workspace Tour (Full & Power tiers only)

Skip this step entirely for Quick tier.

**Display:**

Here's a quick map of your workspace — just the essentials:

- **`documents/`** — Where every generated document goes. PRDs, One-Pagers, analyses, roadmaps. All Markdown, all yours.
- **`context/`** — Your product knowledge: user personas (`USERS.md`), terminology (`TERMINOLOGY.md`), and person pages for stakeholders (`people/`). I read these automatically before generating anything.
- **`global-context/`** — Your product strategy: domain vision, KPIs, roadmap, architecture. Organized per domain, with shared strategic pillars and assumptions. We'll set up the basics next.
- **`to_do's/`** — Your planning system: daily tasks, weekly priorities, commitments, briefings, reviews, and learnings. This is where your planning hierarchy lives — quarter goals cascade down to weekly priorities and daily tasks.
- **`.cursor/rules/`** — My instructions: 14 document templates, 6 reviewer personas, coaching protocols, and formatting preferences. These activate automatically — you don't need to touch them.
- **`.cursor/skills/`** — Multi-step workflows: morning briefing, daily/weekly reviews, meeting notes, meeting prep, competitor analysis, and more.

Everything else (strategy frameworks, web dashboard) is covered in the Onboarding Guide in your browser.

STOP: "Ready to configure your product context?"

ACTION: Update onboarding state — mark `workspace_tour` as completed.

